                            <comment id="14182419" author="ekoifman" created="Fri, 24 Oct 2014 04:29:52 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=thejas&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;thejas&quot;&gt;thejas&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=&quot;https://reviews.apache.org/r/27131/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://reviews.apache.org/r/27131/&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14182969" author="ekoifman" created="Fri, 24 Oct 2014 15:55:44 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=vikram.dixit&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;vikram.dixit&quot;&gt;vikram.dixit&lt;/a&gt; w/o this change, for users to submit Sqoop jobs via WebHCat requires them to modify the Sqoop tar file to include the additional JDBC jars in it which is a major usability issue especially when working with multiple DBs and upgrades.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14182970" author="ekoifman" created="Fri, 24 Oct 2014 15:56:21 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I meant to say in my previous comment that it would be good to get this into 0.14.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
